Solskjær: "If we find the right place for him [Amad] then we'll probably let him go [on loan], if not he'll join our squad probably very soon. He's trained with us and doing really well. I'm sure if he stays with us he'll contribute." #mulive
Solskjær: "He's [Amad] a top player and what he's done in training the last week or so, when he came back from the Olympics, has been really impressive." #mulive

Solskjær asked about the importance of Paul Pogba signing a new contract: "That's going to be the question every week until he does! Paul is a top player and the talks between the club and the representatives I'm not involved in." #mulive
Paul Pogba on #mufc equalling the unbeaten away from home record: "It’s always great, but I prefer to win the league and not have the record." #mulive [mutv]

Paul Pogba: "I think we dropped a few points today — we’re happy we didn’t lose and we get this point with positivity, but we know this game, I think at the end of the season those two points are going to be very important." #mulive [mutv]

Paul Pogba: "I think we deserved more, but you have to show more also on the pitch. After the goal we scored we dropped a little bit, we lost control of the game a bit and that’s why I think we didn’t get the second goal." #mulive [mutv]

Solskjær: "Mason [Greenwood] scores a very good goal, he didn't have one of his best days but he still contributes. When Jadon [Sancho] came on, I thought he looked really sharp for the first 10 or 15 mins but then the whole team fell away.” #mulive

Solskjær on why Martial started against Southampton: “We wanted to get Antho going, to have call it two more forwards, Anthony to drift into the left and Mason [Greenwood]coming inside from the right.” #mulive

Solskjær: “You could see early on, with the fans, it gets the crowd going flying into tackles and we did suffer a few tackles that was part of their [Southampton] thinking early on if you like." #mulive

Solskjær: “We should do better [for Southampton’s goal]. If you don't get a foul, we should make sure we block the shot, put your body on the line and make sure they don't get a strike on target.” #mulive
Southampton's Che Adams: "I think they [Premier League] gave him [Fred] the goal because he doesn't score many." #mulive [bbc]
Mason Greenwood appreciation tweet. https://t.co/e68HHrA0fP

Greenwood: "We've done well [away from home]. It's hard coming away from home to play at these away grounds and with the fans back today it makes a difference but hopefully we can go onto the next game and win." #mulive [bbc]

Greenwood: "I thought it was a foul [on Bruno] but it's the referee's decision at the end of the day and we can't dwell on it. I understand they're going to let more challenges go so the game keeps flowing which is a good idea, but if there's a foul there's a foul." #mulive [bbc]

Mason Greenwood: "There's a little bit of disappointment. I think we should have got all three points with a late goal. Southampton did well. They defended well but I think we should have went for it after the equaliser but unfortunately we didn't." #mulive [bbc]
